    <td width="12"><img src="/images/blank.gif" width="10" height="10" alt="blank.gif (807 bytes)" border="0"></td>
    <td width="488">
    <small><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,Courier New,Courier">Here is how to communicate
    with the Globus Alliance. <br>
    <br>
    <table border="0" width="100%">
      <tr>
        <td width="100%" bgcolor="#FF6633"></font><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,Courier
New,Courier"><small><strong>Technical Questions and
        Problem Reporting</strong></small></font></td>
      </tr>
    </table>

    <p>The Globus Alliance has established a Bugzilla server for tracking
bugs, feature requests, and questions about the Globus Toolkit<sup><font size=-2>TM</font></sup> and
related issues.</p>

<p>To establish a new account, go to the <a href="http://bugzilla.globus.org/bugzilla/">
Globus Alliance Bugzilla page</a> 
and select "Open a new account".  You will then be able to submit new
bugs, and query existing bugs.  There is a <a href="http://bugzilla.globus.org/bugzilla/quicksearch.html">short bug-query form</a> that
lets you search by keyword and a <a href="http://bugzilla.globus.org/bugzilla/query.cgi">more
involved interface</a> that lets you search on many different fields.</p>

    <p>Our <a href="email-archive-search.html">searchable archive</a> of Globus 
    <span lang="en-us">Alliance </span>mailing lists
    provides a rich source of information about the Globus Toolkit and related technologies.
    &nbsp; The <a href="http://www-unix.globus.org/mail_archive/discuss/threads.html">discuss@globus.org</a>
    mailing list in particular is an excellent way to get help with the Globus Toolkit. &nbsp;
    See below for more information about subscribing to this list.</p>
    <table border="0" width="100%">
      <tr>
        <td width="100%" bgcolor="#FF6633"><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,Courier
New,Courier"><small><strong>Mailing Lists</strong></small></font></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p>The Globus Alliance maintains a number of mailing lists for users of 
    the Globus Toolkit.&nbsp; These provide an excellent way to stay in touch
    with others who are using the Toolkit and who share your interests in Grid
    computing.</p>
    <p>Visit the Globus <a href="subscriptions.html">Subscription Center</a> to subscribe to or unsubscribe from
    these mailing lists.</p>

    <table border="0" width="100%">
      <tr>
        <td width="100%" bgcolor="#FF6633"><font face="Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,Courier
New,Courier"><small><strong>Alliance Addresses</strong></small></font></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <p>The following addresses may be used for directing questions about the Globus 
    Alliance to
    us.</p>
    <table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5" width="100%">
